    "<p>Curator of Renaissance and Post-Renaissance Art, Metropolitan Museum of Art.": [],
    "Remington graduated from Harvard University, joining the Metropolitan Museum of Art's Department of Decorative Art in 1923 under <a href=\"/breckj\">Joseph Breck</a>.": [],
    "He remained there the rest of his career.": [],
    "After Breck's death in 1933, the department was divided into the three divisions, medieval art, under <a href=\"/rorimerj\">James Rorimer</a>, Renaissance and Post-Renaissance art, under Remington, and American Art, under Joseph Downs.": [
