    "Remington advanced to the Vice-Directorship of the Department of Renaissance and Post-Renaissance Art.": [],
    "In later years, he held a notorious feud with Greek and Roman curator <a href=\"/bothmerd\">Dietrich von Bothmer</a>, who began in the Museum in 1946.": [],
    "In the 1950s, Remington worked on the installation of the period rooms of the Museum, opened in 1954.": [],
    "Ill health in later years prevented his continued work as Vice Director.": [],
    "Remington published extensively in his Museum's journals on objects in its collection.</p>": []
